---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import aboutImage from "../images/about.png";
---

<BaseLayout title="About · Ben Taylor">
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/home">Home</a>
    <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
    <span aria-current="page">About</span>
  </nav>
  <section class="page-intro">
    <h1 class="hero-title">
      UX Designer <span class="flourish-ampersand">&</span> lead<span
        class="flourish-period">.</span
      >
    </h1>
  </section>

  <section class="card" style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">
    <Image class="about-image" src={aboutImage} alt="Ben Taylor" />
    <p>
      I care about solving meaningful problems and making complex processes feel
      simple. I’m comfortable in ambiguity and good at bringing structure to
      unclear spaces. I work closely with stakeholders to understand what the
      business is trying to achieve, and I use qualitative research to uncover
      what users actually need.
    </p>

    <p>
      As a lead, I focus on giving teams clarity and direction. I make sure
      we’re solving the right problem before moving into solutions, help teams
      work through competing priorities, and keep momentum when things feel
      uncertain. I practise situational leadership — stepping in to guide when
      needed, stepping back to empower when the team has it covered.
    </p>

    <p>
      I stay hands-on in the work. I design and prototype in whatever medium
      makes sense — paper, Figma, code, AI tools — while mentoring others
      through reviews, pairing, and open discussion. I give direct, constructive
      feedback and support people in developing their thinking, not just their
      outputs.
    </p>
    <p>
      My front-end background keeps conversations grounded in what’s
      realistically buildable. I encourage early testing so issues surface
      before development, not after.
    </p>
    <p class="hero-lead">
      <strong>
        I'm focused on outputs that are clear, thoughtful, and genuinely useful.
        If that sounds like what you're looking for, I'd love to chat —
        <a href="/contact">please get in touch</a>.
      </strong>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-image {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
</style>
